{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"210acd00-2a97-4de4-8e4b-ff7eeee0b1d6","content":"In .NET 10, `dotnet test` was rewritten to use Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively. You **no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** — that property was the bridge for older SDKs. You still need `EnableMSTestRunner` to produce the MTP-based executable.\n\nHere's the cleanup:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Mo2abrc5Tn5Pm28za5LxxX","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01CxdnDoVqLQhneDJaqBkCeN","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-1542e19ec9174326bafc3c17727115ac/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-1542e19ec9174326bafc3c17727115ac/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"5c4186aa-e2f1-484a-adf6-a835b05bb0eb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about native MTP support. Let me explain what I know:\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. The .NET 10 SDK's `dotnet test` command was rewritten to use MTP directly.\n\nKey points:\n1. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses MTP natively - no need for `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`\n2. `EnableMSTestRunner` is still needed to make the test project an executable that uses the MSTest runner\n\n\n3. Since MTP is now built into `dotnet test`, the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property becomes unnecessary and can be safely removed from your project configuration.","outputTokens":502},"id":"8bc03ab4-311d-4c84-a659-732d1c2d0c60","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:06:45.040Z","parentId":"4db6694b-bc52-4689-a81d-bfd80c62ffea"}
